A8053 &Cx1f; tdt-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FBN-JAGUARS-BOS &LR;      12-28 0328
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-JAGUARS-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
JAGUARS LIMP INTO PLAYOFF MATCHUP 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By WILL McDONOUGH  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. _ Sunday may have been the rare case when
losing was good for the Patriots.
</P>
<P>
   On paper at least, the Jacksonville Jaguars, the Patriots' foe
in the first round, are the most beat-up team entering the
playoffs.
</P>
<P>
   The Jaguars finish their regular season at home Monday night
against the Steelers with nothing to gain, and are hoping to elude
the injury bug that has haunted them all season.
</P>
<P>
   The Jaguars already have placed 15 men on injured reserve so far
this season, including six starters.
</P>
<P>
   However, the most important factor for the Patriots before the
game is still unknown.
</P>
<P>
   Will quarterback Mark Brunell, the heart and soul of the
Jaguars' offense, be ready to face New England?
</P>
<P>
   Brunell has been out for several weeks with a high ankle sprain,
and it is not known if he will be available against New England.
</P>
<P>
   The Jaguars had to play Jamie Martin, who got hurt, and then
rookie Jonathan Quinn at quarterback, and their high-powered
offense has not been the same.
</P>
<P>
   Brunell told friends last week that he thought he would be ready
for the playoffs, but that was about the same time coach Tom
Coughlin was saying he might be out the rest of the season.
</P>
<P>
   The Patriots have beaten Jacksonville all three times they have
played. New England won twice during its Super Bowl year in 1996,
including in the AFC Championship Game.
</P>
<P>
   Last year, in one of their best wins of Pete Carroll's tenure,
they upset the Jaguars in Jacksonville, triggering a late winning
streak.
</P>
<P>
   When Brunell plays, the Jacksonville offense is explosive.
Running back Fred Taylor has been exceptional, and with Minnesota's
Randy Moss is a candidate to be the NFL's Rookie of the Year.
</P>
<P>
   The Jaguars have lost four defensive linemen for the season,
more than any NFL team.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-12-28-98 0147EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
