<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; 1998 was a banner year in the arts and finance, with
mega-scandals and mega-deals dominating the news. The Boston Globe
offers this look back: &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ENTERTAINMENT/ARTS (e) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   YEAR-OVERVIEW (Undated) -- Pop culture was, of course,
overshadowed by the chief executive soap opera, ``As the White
House Turns,'' in 1998. By Matthew Gilbert. 1650 words.
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   YEAR-SOUNDTRACK (Undated) _ It was the year of the soundtrack.
By Joan Anderman. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
