<P>
   EZZARD-COLUMN _ TIGER, Ga. _ My favorite holiday party wasn't
the cocktail reception with the reindeer ice sculpture we attended
in Atlanta. It wasn't the candle-bedecked dinner that ended in
flamed pudding drama. It was the Christmas potluck supper at the
Tiger firehouse. The action was quite something to behold. (Ezzard,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   GLASS-COLUMN _ WASHINGTON _ We spent the last half of this
century watching TV. In the century to come, television will watch
us. (Glass, Cox News Service) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   KABAT-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ I must confess that during the
holidays I hold a personal grudge against Norman Rockwell. When he
captured forever the idyllic scene of happy, loving family gathered
around a table of bounty, beatific smiles on each cleanly scrubbed
and angelic face, he put thousands of mothers into therapy. (Kabat,
Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED
</P>
