   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MORSE-COLUMN (San Francisco) _ What IF they throw a millennium
party, and no one comes? The year 1998, the year of living
astonishingly, has given Americans a case of amazement burnout. We
cannot be surprised anymore. And as human beings who naturally seek
stability, we fight surprise at every turn. By ROB MORSE.
</P>
