<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-SOCIAL-SECURITY (Washington) _ President Clinton
declares that the computers controlling the nation's Social
Security system are ready for the Year 2000 computer bug, ensuring
that benefits to 48 million older Americans will not be halted in
January 2000. By MARK HELM. (Also filed in the ``f'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   US-IRAQ (Washington) _ U.S. warplanes patrolling in northern
Iraq fire at Iraqi air defenses. President Clinton said the pilots,
who were unharmed, were targeted by surface-to-air missiles and
fired in retaliation. Iraq claims the attack was unprovoked and
killed four soldiers on the ground. By GREG McDONALD.
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   OCTUPLETS-UPDATE (Houston) _ The seven surviving octuplets of
Iyke Louis Udobia and Nkem Chukwu remain in critical condition at a
Houston hospital a day after the most frail of the infants, Odera,
died of heart and lung failure. By LEIGH HOPPER.
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (White Sulphur Springs, W.Va.) _ A tour of the Cold
War atomic bomb shelter beneath the Greenbrier resort here that was
supposed to protect members of Congress demonstrates the folly of
trying to imagine the unimaginable. The shelter would never have
worked. By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   FBN-NFL-COACHES (Undated) _ Four NFL coaches _ Ted Marchibroda,
Ray Rhodes, Dom Capers and Dave Wannstedt _ are fired within a
one-hour period. By JOHN McCLAIN.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-NFL-COWBOYS (Irving, Texas) _ The Dallas Cowboys prepare for
their first-round playoff game after finishing the regular season
with a win over the Washington Redskins. By JODY GOLDSTEIN.
</P>
