<P>
   UNDATED _ By buying Polygram NV two weeks ago, Montreal-based
Seagram instantly became a major player on the international music
scene. The formation of the huge Universal Music Group means that
now everyone from Hole to U2 to Van Morrison to Beck to Marilyn
Manson will be under the same very large umbrella. But it also
means widespread layoffs and leaner rosters, which has a number of
bands worrying about their future. By DAVE FERMAN and MALCOLM
MAYHEW. Story will move in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
