   GA-RURALHOSPITALS _ ATLANTA _ More than 20 rural hospitals in
Georgia have lost money over each of the past three years, and
others have been unprofitable two of the past three years. The
figures are troubling to legislators and businesses in these rural
communities, and will undoubtedly lead to more proposals in next
year's General Assembly. (Miller, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   w/GA-RURALHOSPITALS-TRUST _ ATLANTA _ Lawmakers and patient
advocates question spending associated with the Indigent Care Trust
Fund, which gives some rural hospitals millions, but also gives
their larger, urban counterparts even more funding. (Miller,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) WITH LIST.
</P>
