suffered net losses in the third quarter of 1998, a substantial
increase over a year ago, an industry research firm reported.
(Herubin, Palm Beach Post)
</P>
<P>
   BEAZERHOMES _ Profile of Beazer Homes. It has no intention of
getting caught in a downturn. Just in case one happens next year,
the Atlanta-based builder is fine-tuning a strategy that includes
gaining market share through acquisition; taking short-term options
on land rather than risking ownership; exploring niche markets;
avoiding duplications of competitors' products; and rewarding
employees for saving money internally. Beazer Homes' share price
has jumped nearly 50 percent during the past six weeks. When
stockholders receive their 1998 annual reports within the next few
days, they'll understand why. (Harte, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
MOVED SATURDAY
