   FBC-GATECH-PAGE _ Center Craig Page has been the leader of the
Georgia Tech offensive line throughout the season and has quietly
put together one of the best seasons for an offensive lineman in
Tech history. The 6-foot-3, 300-pounder was named first-team
All-America and was one of three finalists for the Outland Trophy
as the nation's top lineman. More importantly, he helped to
solidify an offensive line that helped lead Tech to a 9-2 record.
Page will play his final game Friday in the Gator Bowl against
Notre Dame. (Rogers, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 22. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   FBC-GATOR-GATECH _ Georgia Tech senior Charlie Rogers is one of
the team's most versatile players, lining up at several positions
on offense during the season, and is one of the main reasons why
the Jackets are 9-2 and playing in the Gator Bowl against Notre
Dame. His versatility was clearly evident in key games down the
stretch and will be key against a strong Notre Dame defense. But
this game means a little more to Rogers, one of several Tech
seniors who hope to end their career with a victory. (Rogers,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
