<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Aboard Neurolab on WPBA tonight
 &HT;    By Bob Longino
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ WPBA heads into space tonight with an hour exploration
of NASA's Neurolab research mission, launched last April aboard
space shuttle Columbia. ``Exploring Frontiers: The Neurolab Space
Shuttle'' (8 p.m.) is pretty much as dry, stiff and by-the-textbook
as the title implies.
</P>
<P>
   The program, produced by WPBA with funding from the Morehouse
School of Medicine(Atlanta, Ga.), shows experiments done on
Columbia to research how space flight affects the human nervous
system.
</P>
<P>
   For sure, it's not a Bruce Willis-led ``Armageddon'' drill team
hoping to knock an asteroid out of harm's way. It's not even John
Glenn returning to space to juice NASA's marketing efforts.
</P>
<P>
   This show is a real-life science fair project, full of good
information and delivered with as little creativity as anyone
anywhere can possibly imagine.
</P>
<P>
   Grade: C
</P>
<P>
   Bob Longino writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   E-mail: channelsurfer(at)ajc.com
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
