</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; For questions about stories, contact  &UR; Frank Perrotta  &LR; at the
Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;  For individual purchase of graphics
or photos please call 212 556-4204 or -1927.
</P>
<P>
   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   IRAQ-NOFLY (New York) _ US warplanes fire at Iraqi air-defense
site in northern Iraq, killing four and wounding seven. Clinton
says enforcement of no-fly zones in north and south of the country
will continue. By Colum Lynch. 1100 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   STOLEN-ART (Boston) -- The Museum of Fine Arts, responding to a
report that it has acquired scores of classical antiquities in
recent years that may have been illegally plundered from grave
sites, says it exercises ``appropriate diligence'' when it acquires
artworks. By Walter V. Robinson. (a, i and e coding)
</P>
<P>
   MA-AUTO-INSURE (Boston) -- Auto insurance rates expected to rise
