<HEADLINE>
CASHMERE AS A NECESSITY  
(JT)
</HEADLINE>
   By ANNE-MARIE SCHIRO    
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Last year, cashmere was considered a luxury. This
season you can find something in cashmere at just about any price
you want to spend.
</P>
<P>
   Lord &AMP; Taylor has cashmere gloves ($30), berets ($40), mufflers
($90), pullovers ($75 to $80) and cardigans ($100 to $120), all in
a range of colors. The Banana Republic stores have hats ($35),
scarves ($65), V-neck shells ($88), T-shirts ($98), vests ($158),
cardigans ($178) and long-sleeve crew necks ($168), in colors like
pale gray, charcoal, plum, black and currant. N. Peal, 5 West 56th
St., has pompom booty socks ($65) and anklets ($75) in pastels and
pale gray.
</P>
<P>
   At Barneys New York, a V-neck pullover in beige, gray, black or
heather blue is $198; a hat in red, teal or yellow is $115. Also at
Barneys, a spaghetti-strap camisole by Aquah in pink, gray, red or
black is $145, and a three-quarter-sleeve pullover with a deep
V-neck by IS in pale blue or navy is $235.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
