<HEADLINE>
TRIPS TO FRANCE, BELGIUM, BERMUDA, FLORIDA 
</HEADLINE>
   (For release Sunday, Jan. 3)  
(rl) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   APRIL ON A BARGE: French Country Waterways has cut prices by
$500 a couple on April barge cruises in Champagne, the upper Loire
and Burgundy. Rates, incorporating the discount, are $2,645 to
$3,745 a person, double occupancy, on departures from April 4 to
25. The five barges on those routes take eight to 18 passengers.
Rates cover accommodations, meals, wines at lunch and dinner, open
bar, tours and excursions and transfers between Paris and the
barges. Reservations: (800) 222-1236, (781) 934-2454 in
Massachusetts.
</P>
<P>
   TWO FOR BRUSSELS: Sabena Belgian World Airlines has expanded its
Valentine's Package offer to eight weekends from Jan. 21 through
March 11. The price of $750 a couple includes round-trip economy
air transportation for two from any of six Sabena gateways in the
United States, two nights at the Brussels Hilton with buffet
breakfast, airport departure taxes and fees. Departures are on
Thursday with returns on the following Sunday. Though the packages
have sold quickly in the past, a substantial number were available
in late December. The package is nonrefundable, and limited to four
seats per call. Reservations: (800) 955-2000 from 8 a.m. to 8:30
p.m. on weekdays and 9 to 5:30 on Saturday and Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   BERMUDA IN WINTER: Three-night getaways to Bermuda from now into
March are available starting at $389 a person, double occupancy.
That price is for a Gogo Worldwide Vacations package from Hartford,
Conn., including round-trip midweek air fare, accommodations at
Grotto Bay Beach Hotel and round-trip airport transfers. A similar
package from New York starts at $469; departures are through March
15. US Airways Vacations has a two-night package starting at $394 a
person, double occupancy, for departures Sunday through Wednesday
from La Guardia Airport through March 28. TNT Vacations'
three-night package starts at $399 a person from Hartford, $444
from either La Guardia or Newark, N.J. Some taxes are additional.
For Gogo Worldwide Vacations, contact a Liberty Travel agency or
call (800) 764-1000. US Airways Vacations can be booked through a
travel agent or by calling (800) 455-0123. For TNT Vacations,
contact a travel agent.
</P>
<P>
   MYSTERY PACKAGE: In connection with the exhibition ``Empires of
Mystery: The Incas, the Andes and Lost Civilizations,'' through
April 25 at the Florida International Museum in St. Petersburg, the
Don Cesar Beach Resort and Spa has a Masterpieces of Mystery
package for $214 a night on Sunday through Thursday that includes a
condominium-style suite, breakfast or lunch for two, and admission
for two to the exhibit, as well as tax and tip. The package costs
$234 a night in the main resort. Weekend prices are $269 and $289
respectively. Reservations: (800) 282-1116.
</P>
