 &UR; YOUR MONEY PACKAGE &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; BANKSTOX &LR;  _ Michael Stead has two traits rare among mutual fund
managers: the shrewdness to sense when stocks could fall and the
bluntness to say so.
</P>
<P>
   Stead manages SIFE Trust Fund, the 37-year-old Walnut Creek fund
that specializes in bank stocks. Six months ago, when bank shares
were near the end of a three-year run that had seen some stocks
triple in value, he sounded the alarm. By Sam Zuckerman
</P>
<P>
   &UR; MONEYBAG &LR;  _ QUESTION: I recently completed graduate school. I
was fortunate enough to receive scholarships and grants this year
totaling more than $15,000. I've been told that I might owe taxes
on some of the money. Please say it isn't so. But if it is, what is
taxable and what isn't? Columnist Arthur M. Louis has the answer.
</P>
