<P>
   ADOPTION-SIBLINGS (Boston) _ Lawyers in a Massachusetts adoption
case have asked the Supreme Court to use it to declare a new
national rule that brothers and sisters have a constitutional right
to be together. Their argument, family law experts say, is at the
forefront of a growing legal movement that is pressing to change
the focus in custody disputes from the rights of adults to the
rights of children. By William Glaberson.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Photo [NYT8) has been sent to NYT photo clients.)
</P>
<P>
   DENVER-DOWNTOWN (Denver) _ The return to downtown living in
eastern cities is well-known but that it is happening in the
automobile-loving cities of the West is part of a new trend that is
expected to take hold over the next few years. One of the cities
viewed by experts as a model is Denver, where a burst of downtown
development is aimed at the returning residents, largely baby
boomers whose kids have grown and left home. By James Brooke.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Locator map has been sent to NYT graphics clients.
Photos [NYT6,7) have been sent to NYT photo clients.)
