<P>
   IMPEACH _ He has the impeachment vote he sought from the House.
Now Rep. Henry Hyde is in search of a strategy for an impeachment
trial in the Senate. On Tuesday, Hyde and the 12 Republican
congressmen he picked to manage President Clinton's Senate trial
will meet for the first time since the historic House vote on Dec.
19 to begin mapping out the prosecution's game plan. By Eric
Schmitt.
</P>
