   ITALY-SPINOFFS (Rome) _ Several of Italy's biggest companies
have said in recent months that they are considering spinoffs or
other separations of large chunks of their real-estate holdings to
increase profit and returns for investors. These companies are
following a Europe-wide trend. By John Tagliabue.
</P>
<P>
   LOCAL-TV-AD-COLUMN (New York) _ The Television Bureau of
Advertising, the trade association that represents local television
broadcasters, is undertaking what is being described as its first
large-scale effort aimed at marketers and agencies to promote the
benefits of running commercials locally rather than nationally. By
Stuart Elliott.
